## 🚀 DEPLOYMENT PATTERNS

### Pattern 1: Zero Mock Deployment Gates
```yaml
The Learning:
  679 mocks almost reached production

Your Implementation:
```bash
# .github/workflows/deploy.yml
name: SDLC 4.9 Deployment

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  validate:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Mock Detection Gate
        run: |
          python scripts/compliance/mock_detection_agent_v3.py
          if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
            echo "❌ MOCKS DETECTED - DEPLOYMENT BLOCKED"
            exit 1
          fi

      - name: Performance Gate
        run: |
          python scripts/compliance/performance_validator.py
          if [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
            echo "❌ PERFORMANCE TARGETS NOT MET"
            exit 1
          fi

  deploy:
    needs: validate
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - name: Blue-Green Deployment
        run: |
          # Deploy to green environment
          kubectl apply -f k8s/green-deployment.yml

          # Test green environment
          ./scripts/validate-deployment.sh green

          # Switch traffic
          kubectl apply -f k8s/green-service.yml

          # Keep blue as backup
          kubectl scale deployment blue --replicas=1
```

### Pattern 2: Crisis-Ready Infrastructure
```yaml
The Learning:
  24-48 hour response requires preparation

Your Setup:
```yaml
# monitoring/alerts.yml
alerts:
  - name: Mock Detection Alert
    condition: mock_count > 0
    severity: CRITICAL
    action: Block deployment + Page team

  - name: Performance Degradation
    condition: response_time > 100ms
    severity: HIGH
    action: Investigate + Scale

  - name: Error Rate Spike
    condition: error_rate > 1%
    severity: HIGH
    action: Rollback consideration

  - name: Crisis Pattern Detected
    condition: matches_known_pattern
    severity: CRITICAL
    action: Activate crisis protocol
