## 🚨 INCIDENT RESPONSE

### Crisis Response Playbook
```yaml
Detection (0-15 min):
  1. Alert received
  2. Assess severity
  3. Check known patterns
  4. Activate team

Response (15-30 min):
  1. Implement quick fix
  2. Monitor impact
  3. Prepare rollback
  4. Communicate status

Resolution (30 min - 48 hr):
  1. Root cause analysis
  2. Permanent fix
  3. Deploy solution
  4. Document pattern

Post-Mortem (Next day):
  1. Timeline review
  2. Decision analysis
  3. Pattern extraction
  4. Playbook update
```

### Rollback Strategy
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# rollback.sh - Battle-tested rollback

echo "🚨 Initiating SDLC 4.9 Crisis Rollback"

# Check current state
CURRENT=$(kubectl get deployment app -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].image}')
echo "Current version: $CURRENT"

# Get previous stable
PREVIOUS=$(kubectl rollout history deployment app | tail -2 | head -1 | awk '{print $1}')
echo "Rolling back to revision: $PREVIOUS"

# Execute rollback
kubectl rollout undo deployment app --to-revision=$PREVIOUS

# Monitor rollback
kubectl rollout status deployment app

# Verify health
./scripts/health-check.sh

# Document incident
echo "Rollback completed. Document pattern for framework evolution."
```

